02:40.750 --> 02:43.583
( man muttering in French )

02:43.625 --> 02:45.667
How do you do?

02:43.625 --> 02:45.667
I'm Chief Burns.

02:45.709 --> 02:47.667
Ah! Americans, yes?

02:47.709 --> 02:50.208
Quelle heure--  No, uh--

02:47.709 --> 02:50.208
What year is this?

02:50.250 --> 02:53.333
What year? I'm sorry, sir,

02:53.375 --> 02:55.667
but who are you exactly?

02:55.709 --> 03:01.000
Ah, how rude of me. So sorry.

02:55.709 --> 03:01.000
My name is Jules...Verne.

03:01.041 --> 03:04.000
Pfft! Not this guy.

03:04.041 --> 03:05.333
Yeah, I'm out.

03:05.375 --> 03:07.208
Did I, uh,

03:05.375 --> 03:07.208
say something wrong?

03:07.250 --> 03:09.291
Well, it's just that

03:07.250 --> 03:09.291
there's a famous author

03:09.333 --> 03:11.834
from the 1800s

03:09.333 --> 03:11.834
named Jules Verne.

03:11.875 --> 03:15.667
Uh, no, no, no. I have written a

03:11.875 --> 03:15.667
few things, but hardly famous.

03:15.709 --> 03:18.625
I'm reading this book at school,

03:15.709 --> 03:18.625
20,000 Leagues Under the Sea.

03:18.667 --> 03:21.041
But it's over

03:18.667 --> 03:21.041
a hundred years old.

03:21.083 --> 03:22.959
You're this Jules Verne?

03:24.125 --> 03:27.375
Uh, no,

03:24.125 --> 03:27.375
I do not recognize this.

03:27.417 --> 03:30.208
He's a fake.

03:27.417 --> 03:30.208
Even I've heard of that book.

03:30.250 --> 03:31.625
And I've never

03:30.250 --> 03:31.625
heard of any books!

03:31.667 --> 03:33.959
Well, if he really is

03:31.667 --> 03:33.959
a time traveler,

03:34.000 --> 03:36.417
he could have come from a point

03:34.000 --> 03:36.417
before he wrote the book.

03:36.458 --> 03:38.333
No way! Fake.

03:38.375 --> 03:40.542
Uh, Kade?

03:42.250 --> 03:45.875
Ugh. Time travel.

03:42.250 --> 03:45.875
I hate time travel!

03:45.917 --> 03:48.792
But how does a hot air balloon

03:45.917 --> 03:48.792
become a time machine?

03:48.834 --> 03:50.375
My balloon! Where is it?

03:50.417 --> 03:52.291
It has something

03:50.417 --> 03:52.291
very important on it.

03:52.333 --> 03:53.875
Heatwave and I

03:52.333 --> 03:53.875
brought it over.

03:53.917 --> 03:55.875
The Bots are

03:53.917 --> 03:55.875
unloading it now.

03:55.917 --> 03:59.208
Heatwave? The Heatwave?

03:59.250 --> 04:01.542
Ca va bien.

03:59.250 --> 04:01.542
Then I am not worried.

04:01.583 --> 04:04.208
Wait, you know about--?

04:01.583 --> 04:04.208
CHASE: Heatwave.

04:04.250 --> 04:06.083
I still maintain

04:04.250 --> 04:06.083
that hot air balloons

04:06.125 --> 04:08.625
are a hard-to-control,

04:06.125 --> 04:08.625
outdated Earth technology.

04:08.667 --> 04:10.417
But they're charming.

04:10.458 --> 04:14.083
Yeah, till you have to untangle

04:10.458 --> 04:14.083
the wreckage from the trees.

04:14.125 --> 04:17.375
( in robotic voice ):

04:14.125 --> 04:17.375
Beep. The other robots

04:14.125 --> 04:17.375
have returned.

04:17.417 --> 04:20.792
Beep, bop, bom.

04:20.834 --> 04:21.709
( Verne chuckles )

04:21.750 --> 04:23.417
Do not pretend for my sake.

04:23.458 --> 04:26.959
On a trip to our future,

04:23.458 --> 04:26.959
I met-- Uh, will meet?

04:27.000 --> 04:30.458
--very advanced, how you say,

04:27.000 --> 04:30.458
la-la-la, Cybertronians.

04:30.500 --> 04:33.000
Oui, oui, oui.

04:33.041 --> 04:35.917
Okay, one:

04:33.041 --> 04:35.917
He knows about Cybertron?

04:35.959 --> 04:38.083
Two: More advanced than us?

04:38.125 --> 04:40.166
And three:

04:38.125 --> 04:40.166
What's "wee, wee, wee"?

04:40.208 --> 04:42.458
It means "yes" in French.

04:42.500 --> 04:44.667
Rescue Bots, meet Jules Verne.

04:44.709 --> 04:47.000
He's visiting.

04:44.709 --> 04:47.000
From the past.

04:47.041 --> 04:49.041
Of France.

04:49.083 --> 04:51.625
Verne?

04:49.083 --> 04:51.625
As in Verne Device?

04:51.667 --> 04:53.709
The instrument

04:51.667 --> 04:53.709
Doctor Morocco uses

04:53.750 --> 04:55.542
to power his

04:53.750 --> 04:55.542
Chamber of Youth.

04:55.583 --> 04:58.083
You know of Thaddeus Morocco?

04:58.125 --> 05:00.041
That is whom

04:58.125 --> 05:00.041
I have come to find.

05:00.083 --> 05:01.625
We are friends.

05:01.667 --> 05:03.542
Any friend of his

05:01.667 --> 05:03.542
can polish my--

05:03.583 --> 05:05.041
Hold on, Heatwave.

05:05.083 --> 05:07.792
Mr. Verne,

05:05.083 --> 05:07.792
maybe you'd better explain.

05:11.834 --> 05:16.208
Thaddeus and I met at

05:11.834 --> 05:16.208
the London Exposition of 1862.

05:16.250 --> 05:18.125
We shared scientific findings,

05:18.166 --> 05:20.041
and soon

05:18.166 --> 05:20.041
I trusted him enough

05:20.083 --> 05:22.000
to give him one of

05:20.083 --> 05:22.000
the two prototype devices

05:22.041 --> 05:24.083
I'd been working on.

05:24.125 --> 05:27.834
But soon after, our interests

05:24.125 --> 05:27.834
went in different directions.

05:27.875 --> 05:29.750
I focused on exploration,

05:29.792 --> 05:32.458
to further the advancement

05:29.792 --> 05:32.458
of mankind.

05:32.500 --> 05:34.000
Thaddeus, it seemed,

05:34.041 --> 05:35.917
worked to advance only one man,

05:35.959 --> 05:40.875
trying to make himself younger,

05:35.959 --> 05:40.875
stronger, wealthier...

05:40.917 --> 05:42.875
I should have intervened,

05:42.917 --> 05:48.250
but I was so caught up in my own

05:42.917 --> 05:48.250
work I let us drift apart.

05:48.291 --> 05:49.458
But just this morning--

05:49.500 --> 05:51.834
Well, this morning in Paris,

05:49.500 --> 05:51.834
1869.

05:51.875 --> 05:53.583
--I received a message.

05:53.625 --> 05:57.500
Consisting only of these

05:53.625 --> 05:57.500
coordinates, and today's date.

05:57.542 --> 06:00.250
And you think the message

05:57.542 --> 06:00.250
was from Morocco?

06:00.291 --> 06:03.125
Who else?

06:00.291 --> 06:03.125
But now, without my balloon,

06:03.166 --> 06:05.667
how am I going

06:03.166 --> 06:05.667
to get back there?

06:05.709 --> 06:07.458
(  dramatic theme playing  )

06:07.500 --> 06:09.458
( dolphins clicking )

06:13.458 --> 06:15.333
Mr. Verne, meet High Tide.

06:15.375 --> 06:17.542
He's been kind enough

06:15.375 --> 06:17.542
to give us transport.

06:19.208 --> 06:20.667
( speaks in French )

06:20.709 --> 06:23.250
Thanks. I think.

06:23.291 --> 06:24.750
Ready to fetch, boy?

06:24.792 --> 06:26.208
Uh-huh, uh-huh.

06:26.250 --> 06:28.750
( box whirring )

06:28.792 --> 06:32.709
(  playful theme playing  )

06:32.750 --> 06:34.667
Ha-ha! Noble!

06:34.709 --> 06:37.834
A boy

06:34.709 --> 06:37.834
and his mechanical dog?

06:37.875 --> 06:40.125
Man's best friend,

06:37.875 --> 06:40.125
they say, no?

06:40.166 --> 06:42.542
Servo's a

06:40.166 --> 06:42.542
Cybertronian helper-Bot.

06:42.583 --> 06:44.000
But he is pretty friendly.

06:44.041 --> 06:47.709
Friendship, young man,

06:44.041 --> 06:47.709
is precious.

06:47.750 --> 06:49.625
Never forget this.

06:49.667 --> 06:52.083
